<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-051-096 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 337 455</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  Sept 30 1991 n1772* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (UK) 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Uncle Sam asks Revenue men to look a new at $1,400m contract withATandamp;T. (US Department of Treasury to reconsider multimillion dollarcontract award to ATandamp;T and Computer Sciences Corp.)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (Contracts)Computer Sciences Corp. (Contracts)International Business Machines Corp. (Cases)Lockheed Corp. (Cases).andO;Topic:     Government AgencyGovernment ContractsContract ProtestsLegal IssuesUnited States. General Services Administration. Board of ContractAppealsUnited States. Department of the TreasuryComputer industry.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>UNCLE SAM ASKS REVENUE MEN TO LOOK ANEWandM;AT $1,400m CONTRACT WITH ATandamp;TandM;Late last week, the US General Services Administration Board of ContractAppeals upheld a protest by IBM Corp and Lockheed Corp over the award of the$1,400m Treasury Microcomputer Acquisition Contract contract to ATandamp;T Co andComputer Sciences Corp for 3,200 Pyramid Technology Corp machines - wiping$1.875 off Pyramid's share price at $16.25 in the process.andP;  The Board did notgo so far as overturning the award, only asking the Treasury Department tosubmit an additional cost justification analysis to support the award toATandamp;T: ATandamp;T's bid was $1,400m, and IBM bid only $708m and the Board found thatthe Internal Revenue Service had failed to conduct a proper price againsttechnical trade-off analysis in accordance with the Request for Proposals.andO;</TEXT></DOC>